<TITLE> 3 arrested as police, Jamaat clash in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  Clashes erupted between police and 'Jamaat-Shibir' protestors in Dhaka on Wednesday as the activists held an unannounced demonstration in the capital's crowded Paltan area, in wake of mass arrests of their members in recent days. Three activists, Shamsul Alam, 18, Monir Hossain, 30, and Ehtesham Billah, 24, were arrested during the clashes, Paltan police said. Jamaat-e-Islami's Dhaka metropolitan unit and the party's supporting student wing Islami Chhatra Shibir gathered in front of Naya Paltan Mosque after Zohr prayers. The group then advanced via Paltan's Culvert Street to the Bijoy Nagar intersection where they held a short meeting. They then marched in a procession towards Paltan Police Station. Police tried to block their path in front of BNP's main office and Ananda Bhaban Community Centre at around 2:30pm, which sparked the clashes. "The Jamaat-Shibir workers held a meeting at Bijoy Nagar turning and then organised the procession without any prior permission. Police were not aware of this sudden programme," Paltan police chief Mujibur Rahman told bdnews24.com. As police tried to stop their procession, the demonstrators pelted police with stones, he said. The resulting 'chase and counter-chase' lasted for some time. At one stage the police were forced to charge with batons to disperse the activists. The police chief sustained injuries to his hand from the pelted stones, he said. Traffic movement between the Kakrail intersection and Paltan Police Station was hampered during the clas
